caption: My favourite restaurant so far in Louisville

My fiance said that it was the best dining experience she has ever had and we have lived all over the country and been fortunate to dine at many great places. A special thanks to Rob, Harold, and Troy. They were unbelievable and made the experience everything you could hope for and more. must try it

A preferred location for quality american food. i should have took a photo of the food but it was too good to interrupt. the service was very helpful and observant. feels like a cafe in phoenix that i enjoyed visiting.

If you have never had a hot brown, this is the place to have one. But if you do, then you won't have room for any appetizers or one of the wonderful entrees (grilled duck breast anyone?) that are part of the selection. An excellent wine list BUT ALSO a wonderful bourbon selection of craft and small batch bourbons as a great start or end to your meal. White table cloth, classy waiters and an amazing yesteryear atmosphere.
Did not go here, I must have been in the vicinity
Beautiful place to go back in time and experience food and atmosphere in days gone by. Just lovely!

My husband and I had dinner here last night for our 29th wedding anniversary dinner. And I really loved it!! We had the famous hot brown and absolutely loved it, also The kentucky derby drink was delicious! From the ambiance, mood lighting, , great food and wonderful service. It was 5 stars and I would recommend to everyone !!
Great experience

We are bummed English Grill.   My husband called and made reservations for Valentines Day a few weeks ago.  He got a call just now confirming our reservation and telling us that there is a special menu for the night, of which a good part of is seafood.  I don't eat seafood.  And nowhere on the website, that I can find, does it say there will be a special menu for Valentines Day.  So now we are screwed because we can't get another reservation because most all other placees are booked because its Valentine's Day.
Staff were extremely friendly and accommodating.
Excellent service, fantastic food.

There are pretenders to the Hot Brown. This ain't one of 'em! This is the birthplace of this iconic dish, and at 90+ years of age, it is still going strong! Our two guests had had pretender HBs before, but all four of us will never go for anything less than the real thing from now on!  I regret not taking a photo of the Hot Brown, but I'll show you photos of the lobster bisque and crab cake appetizers, both of which were excellent. As you can see, the dishes were also visually appealing.  Rob E and Harold were very attentive, providing excellent, informative, and entertaining service. It was an outstanding evening and we will certainly return!
Do. Not. Miss.
A few special places provide a perfect  dining experience, English Grill is one.  Every time.  Impeccable service.
Great atmosphere. Amazing Services. Great atmosphere.
This place was good. I went with my friend. We spend great time. Amazing services. Great atmosphere. Room was clean and well managed. Great location.

FAVORITE PLACE In the Brown Hotel, English Grill was closed, but the restaurant was open.  We had a hot brown.  It was my first time trying it, but it is excellent.  They also had a brown Manhattan.  Historic hotel and restaurant.  Valet parking is free if you eat at the restaurant.

We went there for our 20th  wedding anniversary. the food, service were outstanding. We were told a little Louisville history while we were there and that led us to doing other things while we were in town

One of the best dinning experiences in Louisville, excellent service, warm environment they make us feel like at home, the chef and the servers are experts, they really know what they are doing and what they are offering

Our evening at The English Grill was magnificent ! All of the staff were excellent and made us feel like we were cherished friends! Special thanks to Yassir and George for making us feel welcomed. The food was top shelf. The "Hot Brown" is a must try. We will definitely return!
Super dinner in this historic restaurant. Very polished place but you dont have to dress formal to come here. Food was very well designed and resonably priced.
Two words - "Hot Brown", a must have, available at the Grill or Lobby Bar.
The service is first class

Old world grandeur. Five star service. Staff was wonderful and very attentive. Had to have to original Hot Brown...it did not disappoint! Wife had their pasta dish with brussel sprouts. Desserts were very rich. Expensive, but worth it every now and then.
Headed to a show at the Brown Theatre and stopped in for a bite. The symphony of what they are calling the Shrimp & Grits was probably my favorite meal this year. Will return.
What a nice fancy place. I found out it is the birthplace of one of my favorite Pittsburgh dishes!!

Take your time and enjoy the experience. Start with the Caesar salad that is prepared table side. The English Grill is a favorite for our family especially around the holidays. The servers always have fantastic stories about the food or the hotel. If you don't know what to order just ask for the Hot Brown.
Expensive but excellent

Let me tell you. This place was great. I booked a night at the hotel for my friend and I and made a reservation at the English Grill for dinner. We both had the hot brown and it was delicious. The chef also brought us new food from the menu for us to try. I had no idea what I ate but it was amazing. The English grill went the extra mile and surprised us with an Ice Cream Sunday for our anniversary. Take a piece of advice from this random stranger. Buy a couple of drinks, go to the English Grill and have a great night.

What a great experience at the English Grill.  You can eat dinner at plenty of "old school" Louisville restaurants, but what makes an experience is the staff.  Kelly A. our waiter was excellent.  Very attentive and easy to talk with.  He knew exactly when to come and chat and when to give us some time to eat and enjoy the ambiance.  He knew the history of the hotel and  had several interesting stories.   Arnold, for lack of a better term, "table attendant" was excellent.  He has been at the restaurant for over 25 years.  I appreciated his dedication and his pleasant service.  We had the lobster bisque which was excellent, the catch of the day which was sea bass (cooked perfectly) with risotto and I added the lobster tail.  We had shrimp & grits as an app and it was excellent. My wife had the filet with asparagus and she really enjoyed it.  I highly recommend the restaurant.  Thank you Kelly, thank you Arnold.  Thank you chef.  I hope everyone has the opportunity to have such a nice experience.
Perfect.  Food was fantastic.   Service even better.

This was a special experience for our family. They took great care of us and everyone seemed to want to please like you just dont see very often. Its in the beautiful lobby of the Brown Hotel. The food was very nicely done with a lot of special touches. Not nearly as expensive as we thought it would be.
Great place. But it has a dress code that excludes people like me.
The New York Strip was the best steak I've ever had

I made these reservations online several weeks ago for me and my boyfriend on Valentine’s Day.  Needless to say I picked the restaurant because it looked classy from the images, and the menu items I saw looked amazing - I just knew this place would be perfect. I totally had my heart set on their roast duck, and creme brûlée for dessert.  I live in Washington, DC and flew here to Louisville so that we could have a romantic week/end together.  Anyway, we went through the restaurant website that redirected us to OpenTable to make our reservations.  When we got there we were super excited to order and begin our first V-Day together.  And then I glanced down at my plate and saw a neatly folded, decorated card and no signs of a full menu.  I knew what it meant before I even opened it, and to my utter disappointment, I was confirmed in my assumption: a pre fixe menu (they only have one option. You don’t get to pick your meal - they have picked it for you and do not allow any alterations or substitutions. You’re stuck with whatever the chef came up with for that night).  My heart literally dropped.  It wouldn’t have come as such a blow if we’d known this in advance.  But the restaurant had been advertising their FULL MENU everywhere!!  There was no ad or notice warning patrons that there would be a fixed menu that night, as is customary when serving pre fixe for obvious reasons). My boyfriend was prepared for the cost of dining at this particular restaurant, but he also wasn’t willing to pay $100/plate for food we barely wanted - certainly nothing I had had my heart set on for weeks.  Ugh, it was so disappointing it was crushing. Evening totally ruined.  Our reservations were for 9:45pm, so by the time we realized this discrepancy and began looking for an alternative, almost everything else within reach was closing or not accepting walk-ins.  We ended up having to order burritos from some rinky little joint on the way back, dressed in semi-formal clothes which made it obvious to people that we either missed our reservations or had some issue with our original plans.  I mean, decked out to the nines in a burrito shack!  I felt so humiliated, glad we ordered our food to go so people wouldn’t look at me and think I was out with a guy who would take me out to essentially a fast food restaurant for Valentine’s.  So, they get one star for effectively ruining my first Valentine’s Day with my boyfriend with piss-poor advertisement.
Amazing! The food was wonderful and our waiter was wonderful! Can't wait to go back sometime.

It’s worth every penny. Between the service and the history lesson this place is 5 stars. If you add the fantastic food, it’s 10 stars. This place is to die for! I will be back very soon, this is one of my new favorite downtown restaurants.
Great experience! Amazing food and service. Highly recommend for fine dine experience.

Not good... service was good, but food was just not good-very disappointed. We had the crab cake app which was 1 crab cake the size of a quarter with no flavor and plating was not appealing-I might as well have spent $15 on another drink. For dinner, again, the pork chop was terrible-absolutely no taste. The place was not full and we waited a while for the food. If you go, stick with the hot brown. It is great, but seriously, I would be hesitant to get anything else. The table next to us sent back their steak.
Exquisite!
Excellent food and service at the historical Brown Hotel.
Great old fashion service great hot brown

Best place in Louisville for a special occasion. My wife and I visited this beautiful and historic restaurant again tonight. Troy Ritchie and his wonderful staff always impress with their attention to detail. Our waiter tonight was Rob, who offered us superior service with all of those who helped him make our evening so enjoyable. Harold, from the wait staff, remember us from the previous times we were there, and he always delights us with his service and stories. The entire place is warm and cozy and ever so romantic. It's truly our favorite place to come for a wonderfully delicious and delightful dinner experience! We look forward to our next visit, and thank you so much again!!!!
Always flawless...no matter your app, entree, dessert or beverage selections... perfect every single time.
Always great!
A Louisville tradition for 95years
Got to be my favorite restaurant in Louisville. Such a warm feeling when I call me about the staff and the food is great
Great dinning experience and friendly staff.

From the moment we walked in the staff were very welcoming. The food was delicious our waiter Rob was great. The room was beautiful the whole experience is definitely worth going for. It was a very romantic setting and very enjoyable. I recommend this restaurant to anyone who wants to get there time an money's worth.

If you have not ate at the English Grill you haven't lived. I went and the waiter Rob was not only great but knowledgeable about the history of the hotel and restaurant. Thanks to the whole staff and can't forget the chef.
Lovely appetizers in Lobby Bar!!
Great food at a good price

The filet mignon was excellent. The duck was delicious and cooked perfectly. The bread pudding was outstanding. Our waiter (Kelly) was knowledge, gracious, professional, and personable. The ambience is elegant, and it is quiet enough to have a conversation with one's table mates. I enjoyed it very much and will recommend to anyone looking for a lovely meal and experience. Valet parking is free (validated with meal). Not suitable for children.
I like got the ky hot bown they he'd there

Amazing! We celebrated our anniversary at the English Grill and were blown away by the food, the service, and the experience. Chef Dustin Willett prepared an amazing meal which we will remember the rest of our lives. The classic elegant decor and attentive service were first class. We would recommend the English Grill for anyone who wants a truly good and memorable evening. Thank you!
An absolutely amazing experience for my Wife and I’s anniversary. The food was outstanding and for as good as the food was the service was better.
Excellent food and atmosphere
Original Hot Browns... so delicious! Wonderful bread before meal and dessert after as well. Waiter was super friendly and took very good care of us, as did Harold, who’s worked there for years.
The most elegant place in Louisville with the feel of the old authentic Louisville. A true historical gem. Worth every penny.

Worst dining experience of my life. The staff was horrible and rude. If not for the food being delicious, I'd have given them a 0 rating. My wife left practically in tears because of the portentous attitudes we experienced.  In all my life we've never been subjected to such horrible service and will never go back even if it were free.

We had an awesome NYE experience! We had the late night hot brown and I­t­ was obviously the best in town! George was a gracious server and could not have been more friendly. I would recommend this to anyone for a great NYE in Louisville!

Being from Louisville, I've felt a bit incomplete loving hot browns and not having had one from The Brown. I must say it lived up to the hype. My most common complaint for a hot brown is when they don't have enough sauce. The chef here did not make this mistake and filled the serving dish! A symphony of flavors danced upon my tongue during every bite. But it didn't stop there... The service was excellent. Every member of the staff was friendly and ready to share the history of the hotel and the famous dish. They even gave us a copy of the recipe for us to try and make our own at home. I highly recommend a stop in here for one if you are a hot brown fan!
We had a lovely dinner at the English Grill last night, celebrating a friend's birthday! The food, service, and ambiance were outstanding🍴🍷
Great food and even better service! Best mac n cheese on the planet and the butter pecan torte was to die for! Very pricey but experience is worth the money.
Good services! We got a complementary dessert for our anniversary.
Best meal of my life.
The brown pretty well has the best of everything it's just very expensive
"Fried 'hot' chicken and biscuits and gravy for the main course."

The restaurant was lovely and the staff was excessively friendly and enjoyable to talk with.  Ron, our server, had a great knowledge of the menu and was very personable. He described the sweet potato soup so well that we had to try it.  We thought that it was very tasty, however we weren't quite prepared for the cayane pepper that gave it a very spicy kick. It was a little too much for my wife to handle, even though she really enjoyed the soup overall. She ordered that salmon and was very impressed by it. I had come intending to try the famous hot brown. The dish was so hot that I couldn't take a bite for several minutes. The bacon and turkey was good, however the gravy and cheese overwhelmed me. I usually clean my plate, but I had to stop with several bites left on the plate. We enjoyed ourselves, and we were glad we came, however we will probably try something different next time.
We had a very nice Valentine dinner.
needs more sauce

“First rate” Feels like going back in time. Sit in the lounge and listed to a superb guy on the piano while watching the hustle around the lobby. Great bourbon selection and staff that can talk about it all day, particularly the manager, who roams the lobby a lot.
Amazing décor. Feels like it must have 100 years ago. Interesting equestrian theme. Well trained staff. Chef has a nice touch. Service staff know the menu well. I loved the tableside cooking.
Excellent food coupled with great decor...
Great Time Great Food Great Service

Beautiful dining room, great service, good food but not the best.  I tried a good watermelon-mozzarella appetizer/tasting, their homemade bread was good, and the classic Hot Brown was good but the flavors weren't as strong as  I was hoping.  My colleague enjoyed their gin and tonic. I might come back sometime just for the beautiful, classy environment and cocktails.
Love it
